1
00:00:00,959 --> 00:00:05,672
[brazen music playing]

2
00:00:10,969 --> 00:00:11,803
‪[electronic blipping]

3
00:00:17,100 --> 00:00:18,518
The entire batch was intercepted.

4
00:00:18,601 --> 00:00:20,228
- [Regalia] <i>All the ivory?</i>
- [Red] <i>Yes, Dad.</i>

5
00:00:20,311 --> 00:00:22,522
[Regalia] <i>You told me</i>
<i>everything's going well.</i>

6
00:00:22,605 --> 00:00:24,566
Your men failed again!

7
00:00:24,649 --> 00:00:25,775
[Mongki] <i>This is all that meddler's fault.</i>

8
00:00:25,859 --> 00:00:27,777
<i>He completely ruined the operation.</i>

9
00:00:27,861 --> 00:00:29,904
<i>But no one saw that meddler's face</i>

10
00:00:29,988 --> 00:00:31,406
<i>because he was too fast and skilled.</i>

11
00:00:32,157 --> 00:00:33,783
[Delfin] <i>They found a tumor in my brain.</i>

12
00:00:33,867 --> 00:00:34,951
<i>Malignant.</i>

13
00:00:35,035 --> 00:00:37,996
God is punishing me for the sins
I've committed against my family!

14
00:00:38,079 --> 00:00:40,373
[Siony] <i>Father, is this really happening?</i>

15
00:00:40,457 --> 00:00:43,001
[Peping] Did you notice
who brought the saint back?

16
00:00:43,084 --> 00:00:43,918
Brought back?

17
00:00:44,002 --> 00:00:45,253
[Atoy] Oh, wow, it's here!

18
00:00:45,336 --> 00:00:46,337
[Red] <i>I will find him.</i>

19
00:00:46,421 --> 00:00:47,380
No one crosses a Regalia.

20
00:00:48,256 --> 00:00:49,716
My time is almost up.

21
00:00:49,799 --> 00:00:52,260
Atoy, no. Your dad has cancer.

22
00:00:52,927 --> 00:00:55,513
- [Cita] <i>Please don't leave him.</i>
- [Atoy] <i>Is it true?</i>

23
00:00:55,597 --> 00:00:58,183
Treatment and check-ups
won't make any difference at this point.

24
00:00:58,266 --> 00:00:59,768
[Cita] <i>If you can humble yourself,</i>

25
00:01:00,435 --> 00:01:02,645
<i>do it now, while there's still time,</i>

26
00:01:02,729 --> 00:01:04,439
<i>while there's still a chance.</i>

27
00:01:04,522 --> 00:01:05,774
<i>Before it's too late.</i>

28
00:01:05,857 --> 00:01:07,192
[Paldo] <i>Who brought it back here?</i>

29
00:01:07,275 --> 00:01:08,401
He did.

30
00:01:09,152 --> 00:01:10,320
[Nestor] Tell them the truth, Atoy!

31
00:01:10,403 --> 00:01:13,073
[Cita] And to whoever stole
Saint Anthony of Padua,

32
00:01:13,156 --> 00:01:14,741
yikes, karma's got your number.

33
00:01:14,824 --> 00:01:15,700
[crowd buzzing]

34
00:01:15,784 --> 00:01:16,868
‪[indistinct chatter]

35
00:01:20,747 --> 00:01:25,084
[gun firing]

36
00:01:27,045 --> 00:01:28,046
[in English] Dad.

37
00:01:29,506 --> 00:01:33,802
I’m already tracking down
whoever caused our setback.

38
00:01:34,969 --> 00:01:35,804
[in English] What for?

39
00:01:36,429 --> 00:01:39,265
Do you really think you can
restore the client’s trust

40
00:01:39,349 --> 00:01:40,642
after that failure?

41
00:01:40,725 --> 00:01:43,102
- [somber music playing]
- [gun firing]

42
00:01:43,686 --> 00:01:45,188
I just want to teach them a lesson!

43
00:01:46,773 --> 00:01:51,402
I've learned a hard lesson
when your sibling left,

44
00:01:52,403 --> 00:01:55,406
and I don’t want that to happen again,
now that we have her.

45
00:01:56,407 --> 00:01:57,534
[gun firing]

46
00:02:02,705 --> 00:02:03,832
Doctor Escover.

47
00:02:04,332 --> 00:02:06,126
[stirring music playing]

48
00:02:06,209 --> 00:02:10,380
[in English] Mr. Regalia, I have here
the results of Miss Audrey's tests.

49
00:02:11,131 --> 00:02:12,966
[in English] Anything
we should be worried about?

50
00:02:14,801 --> 00:02:16,719
[suave music playing]

51
00:02:16,803 --> 00:02:18,429
FATHER'S LANE
FOOD HUB IN BACLARAN

52
00:02:58,136 --> 00:03:00,138
[sewing machine whirring]

53
00:03:00,722 --> 00:03:01,681
[Emerson] Thank goodness!

54
00:03:02,515 --> 00:03:04,309
Our town fiest will be joyful again!

55
00:03:04,392 --> 00:03:06,227
The patron is finally back!

56
00:03:06,311 --> 00:03:07,645
All thanks to Atoy!

57
00:03:07,729 --> 00:03:08,730
Happy Fiesta soon!

58
00:03:08,813 --> 00:03:10,064
[Emerson] But he insists
he didn’t bring it back!

59
00:03:10,148 --> 00:03:11,858
Whatever, I'm still Team Atoy!

60
00:03:11,941 --> 00:03:14,319
Like we even have another choice.
I'm on Team Atoy too!

61
00:03:14,402 --> 00:03:15,945
- I'm so proud of my wife.
- Oh!

62
00:03:19,490 --> 00:03:24,621
[pensive music playing]

63
00:03:56,236 --> 00:03:57,237
[sighs]

64
00:04:00,740 --> 00:04:01,950
Even if you don't admit it,

65
00:04:02,909 --> 00:04:07,288
I know you were the one
who returned the patron.

66
00:04:09,666 --> 00:04:15,463
Were you involved in the incident
at the port with the container van?

67
00:04:22,887 --> 00:04:24,931
Well, none of that matters anymore.

68
00:04:25,974 --> 00:04:27,642
What truly matters is that you’re safe.

69
00:04:29,602 --> 00:04:30,979
All thanks be to God.

70
00:04:32,480 --> 00:04:36,401
And endless gratitude to Saint Anthony
for bringing you back to us safely.

71
00:04:36,943 --> 00:04:38,653
Finally, everything is back to normal.

72
00:04:40,697 --> 00:04:45,994
I wish Saint Anthony could also
heal hearts and take back feelings.

73
00:04:47,662 --> 00:04:50,164
Uh… What do you mean?

74
00:04:50,832 --> 00:04:53,293
I wish he could take away
your anger toward me,

75
00:04:55,378 --> 00:04:57,422
so you could finally forgive me

76
00:04:58,006 --> 00:05:00,591
for the wrongs I've done
to you and your mother.

77
00:05:13,146 --> 00:05:14,647
‪[pensive music playing]

78
00:05:14,731 --> 00:05:17,275
I wonder if he could also
restore your health.

79
00:05:21,779 --> 00:05:23,531
I can't believe
you've been praying for me.

80
00:05:28,119 --> 00:05:30,371
Dad, you really should see a doctor.

81
00:05:32,665 --> 00:05:34,667
There might be a new treatment,

82
00:05:34,751 --> 00:05:38,421
and it could help us know
what to do to make you better.

83
00:05:41,299 --> 00:05:44,052
I've accepted my fate a long time ago.

84
00:05:47,138 --> 00:05:51,309
I hope you can learn to accept it too.

85
00:05:54,187 --> 00:05:57,356
There's no point in debating doctor visits

86
00:05:58,983 --> 00:06:00,860
because my fate is already sealed,

87
00:06:03,654 --> 00:06:05,448
and my time is almost up.

88
00:06:13,748 --> 00:06:18,461
If there's something
you want to pursue in life,

89
00:06:22,173 --> 00:06:24,092
don't let it stop you.

90
00:06:24,175 --> 00:06:26,344
[gentle music playing]

91
00:06:26,427 --> 00:06:29,055
This is your life, your world.

92
00:06:30,223 --> 00:06:31,808
Don't let my situation hold you back.

93
00:06:41,526 --> 00:06:42,401
You know, Dad,

94
00:06:45,530 --> 00:06:49,700
if there’s one thing I know I’m good at,

95
00:06:51,577 --> 00:06:53,079
it’s finding things.

96
00:06:57,125 --> 00:07:00,878
Finding those… things that are lost.

97
00:07:01,796 --> 00:07:03,548
[scoffs] I’m a tracker, after all.

98
00:07:07,510 --> 00:07:09,137
But when I returned here,

99
00:07:13,349 --> 00:07:15,977
I never realized that I was the one
who had been lost.

100
00:07:20,064 --> 00:07:21,691
I suppose that’s just how people are.

101
00:07:23,901 --> 00:07:25,945
There are parts of us
that truly go missing.

102
00:07:28,281 --> 00:07:29,866
Versions of ourselves that vanish.

103
00:07:32,452 --> 00:07:35,663
Pieces of who we used to be.

104
00:07:39,834 --> 00:07:41,002
But you know, Dad…

105
00:07:44,172 --> 00:07:45,423
when I’m with you,

106
00:07:49,719 --> 00:07:51,429
I end up finding myself again.

107
00:07:55,224 --> 00:07:56,267
So, Dad…

108
00:08:00,563 --> 00:08:02,231
Dad, I'm staying with you.

109
00:08:07,487 --> 00:08:09,280
I'm never leaving your side.

110
00:08:09,363 --> 00:08:13,784
[sentimental music playing]

111
00:08:48,903 --> 00:08:51,030
‪[music concludes]

112
00:08:54,158 --> 00:08:56,118
[gun firing on video]

113
00:08:56,202 --> 00:08:58,120
That shot's way too far.

114
00:08:58,204 --> 00:08:59,956
How are we even supposed to identify him?

115
00:09:00,039 --> 00:09:04,585
Sir, that's the best CCTV footage
our contact has.

116
00:09:05,211 --> 00:09:06,295
[Red] Whatever.

117
00:09:06,379 --> 00:09:09,465
Just see to it you track down the guy
who sabotaged our operations.

118
00:09:11,801 --> 00:09:12,677
[menacing music playing]

119
00:09:12,760 --> 00:09:14,929
I'm definitely going to make
that bastard pay.

120
00:09:18,349 --> 00:09:20,184
[in English] Bang! Bang!

121
00:09:26,232 --> 00:09:28,943
SIR DELFIN'S
TAILORING SHOP

122
00:09:34,448 --> 00:09:35,283
‪[wheel squeaking]

123
00:09:55,219 --> 00:09:56,429
Do you still remember how?

124
00:09:58,764 --> 00:09:59,849
[Delfin chuckles]

125
00:09:59,932 --> 00:10:00,975
Go on.

126
00:10:02,101 --> 00:10:03,936
Make me a new suit.

127
00:10:04,020 --> 00:10:06,939
But I'll be the one choosing the fabric.

128
00:10:07,523 --> 00:10:11,485
Why? What do you need a suit for?

129
00:10:11,569 --> 00:10:15,948
[light feel-good music playing]

130
00:10:17,742 --> 00:10:18,701
[chuckles]

131
00:10:19,535 --> 00:10:20,453
Don't ask.

132
00:10:21,078 --> 00:10:25,207
Just make me one,
so you can start practicing again.

133
00:10:26,292 --> 00:10:32,632
You see, I believe everyone
deserves a proper suit.

134
00:10:33,466 --> 00:10:37,219
Not to look perfect,

135
00:10:38,512 --> 00:10:43,726
but to remind us that we're all unique

136
00:10:45,186 --> 00:10:49,106
and… tailor-made.

137
00:10:53,277 --> 00:10:54,945
[Delfin] <i>Throughout a person's life,</i>

138
00:10:55,529 --> 00:10:56,781
<i>they tailor themselves.</i>

139
00:10:57,865 --> 00:11:00,493
<i>Every experience is a stitch,</i>

140
00:11:00,576 --> 00:11:04,080
<i>every mistake a seam.</i>

141
00:11:04,163 --> 00:11:05,247
<i>And every love?</i>

142
00:11:06,040 --> 00:11:08,501
<i>That's the thread</i>
<i>that binds it all together.</i>

143
00:11:13,756 --> 00:11:15,299
<i>We, as tailors,</i>

144
00:11:15,383 --> 00:11:17,385
<i>know that the hidden stitches</i>

145
00:11:17,468 --> 00:11:20,763
<i>are just as important</i>
<i>as the visible ones on the outside.</i>

146
00:11:21,514 --> 00:11:23,849
<i>That is how a person's</i>
<i>character should be,</i>

147
00:11:23,933 --> 00:11:28,145
<i>upright, even in times</i>
<i>when no one else is watching.</i>

148
00:11:28,229 --> 00:11:31,148
[hissing]

149
00:11:31,232 --> 00:11:33,734
[light, feel-good music playing]

150
00:11:33,818 --> 00:11:35,945
[hissing]

151
00:12:19,989 --> 00:12:23,325
[music slows down]

152
00:12:28,289 --> 00:12:31,125
[Delfin] <i>Because when we die,</i>

153
00:12:31,208 --> 00:12:34,295
<i>what really matters is that</i>
<i>we've stitched our lives</i>

154
00:12:34,378 --> 00:12:36,213
<i>and our relationships carefully,</i>

155
00:12:36,297 --> 00:12:40,301
<i>so that's what the people we leave behind</i>
<i>will carry in their hearts.</i>

156
00:12:41,093 --> 00:12:42,261
[humming]

157
00:12:49,101 --> 00:12:50,478
My master cutter is one of a kind!

158
00:12:51,145 --> 00:12:52,146
You can finally manage.

159
00:12:52,730 --> 00:12:55,774
Of course, I learned from the very best.

160
00:12:56,609 --> 00:12:57,485
[chuckles softly]

161
00:12:58,402 --> 00:13:00,821
Um, just adjust it a little.

162
00:13:01,614 --> 00:13:03,491
It's a bit short…

163
00:13:03,574 --> 00:13:06,619
I want you to make me
look my absolute best.

164
00:13:15,377 --> 00:13:22,259
I'm sorry for not supporting
what you wanted back then.

165
00:13:23,511 --> 00:13:26,555
The truth is, I just didn't
want you to leave.

166
00:13:27,431 --> 00:13:31,685
Losing your mother
was already painful enough.

167
00:13:33,854 --> 00:13:34,897
That's it.

168
00:13:35,397 --> 00:13:36,232
‪[deep breath]

169
00:13:36,982 --> 00:13:40,736
But as the saying goes,

170
00:13:41,320 --> 00:13:46,200
parents are meant to teach
their children how to use their wings.

171
00:13:47,326 --> 00:13:49,453
And then, let them fly freely.

172
00:13:50,037 --> 00:13:50,871
You know…

173
00:13:51,622 --> 00:13:53,624
It's a good thing you didn't
listen to me back then.

174
00:13:55,209 --> 00:13:56,335
Because look at you now.

175
00:13:57,378 --> 00:13:59,880
You've come so far in your career.

176
00:14:02,967 --> 00:14:04,301
I'm so proud of you.

177
00:14:07,638 --> 00:14:08,514
[younger Delfin] <i>Just keep it straight.</i>

178
00:14:08,597 --> 00:14:10,099
Is that good enough for you?

179
00:14:11,600 --> 00:14:14,645
Or should we adjust it a little?
Oh, is it too tight here?

180
00:14:14,728 --> 00:14:16,897
- [laughing]
- Too tight, too tight, huh?

181
00:14:16,981 --> 00:14:19,149
- Dad.
- [in English] Up!

182
00:14:20,067 --> 00:14:21,193
[in English] Up!

183
00:14:21,277 --> 00:14:23,320
[laughing]

184
00:14:24,697 --> 00:14:27,741
- Dad.
- [laughing]

185
00:14:48,596 --> 00:14:50,556
SIR DELFIN'S
TAILORING SHOP

186
00:14:57,313 --> 00:15:00,316
Son, remember my request, okay?

187
00:15:01,150 --> 00:15:01,984
Just leave it to me.

188
00:15:02,067 --> 00:15:03,694
Where do you want it?
By the pocket or the cuff?

189
00:15:06,739 --> 00:15:07,823
[Delfin] Here.

190
00:15:16,957 --> 00:15:21,378
[sentimental music playing]

191
00:15:22,838 --> 00:15:24,632
Is there still a lot to fix?

192
00:15:25,299 --> 00:15:26,342
I guess.

193
00:15:37,478 --> 00:15:38,437
As for me…

194
00:15:39,021 --> 00:15:39,939
I only have one more thing to fix.

195
00:15:40,022 --> 00:15:44,026
[breathing heavily]

196
00:15:46,820 --> 00:15:48,030
I'm sorry for…

197
00:15:51,742 --> 00:15:53,786
the mistakes I made back then.

198
00:15:56,747 --> 00:15:58,666
Believe it or not…

199
00:16:01,877 --> 00:16:03,504
it only happened once.

200
00:16:06,799 --> 00:16:08,467
I loved your mother.

201
00:16:09,134 --> 00:16:11,804
[sobbing]

202
00:16:16,725 --> 00:16:17,643
She was…

203
00:16:18,727 --> 00:16:20,729
She was the only woman I ever loved.

204
00:16:21,397 --> 00:16:23,023
[Delfin mumbles]

205
00:16:25,234 --> 00:16:26,443
Dad, it's okay.

206
00:16:28,153 --> 00:16:28,988
[softly] Forget about it.

207
00:16:38,789 --> 00:16:40,708
Anyway, this isn't the final fitting yet.

208
00:16:42,918 --> 00:16:45,838
[gentle music playing]

209
00:16:45,921 --> 00:16:48,966
Do we need to make any more adjustments?

210
00:16:50,551 --> 00:16:57,516
[sobbing] There's something I've
been meaning to tell you…

211
00:16:59,143 --> 00:17:03,605
I've looked into alternative medicine,

212
00:17:04,273 --> 00:17:09,445
and there are clinical trials
you might quality for.

213
00:17:10,779 --> 00:17:12,072
We have the means anyway,

214
00:17:12,156 --> 00:17:13,615
and I'll take care of you.

215
00:17:13,699 --> 00:17:16,118
Atoy, son…

216
00:17:18,537 --> 00:17:20,539
We've already talked about this.

217
00:17:23,000 --> 00:17:24,460
There's no need to bother.

218
00:17:28,088 --> 00:17:29,048
I'm good.

219
00:17:35,220 --> 00:17:36,055
‪[exhales]

220
00:18:13,967 --> 00:18:15,094
Dude, I'm amazed.

221
00:18:15,761 --> 00:18:17,721
I didn't know the boss was filthy rich.

222
00:18:19,139 --> 00:18:20,557
[Mongki] Consider yourself lucky.

223
00:18:20,641 --> 00:18:22,643
Not everyone gets the chance
to get in here.

224
00:18:29,358 --> 00:18:30,734
- [Mongki] Sir.
- [Paldo] Sir.

225
00:18:30,818 --> 00:18:31,902
[Paldo] Good morning, sir.

226
00:18:31,985 --> 00:18:32,861
‪[gaming fight sounds]

227
00:18:32,945 --> 00:18:33,821
Who are you?

228
00:18:34,488 --> 00:18:36,740
Sir, he's Paldo.

229
00:18:36,824 --> 00:18:39,785
He was the one who stole the Saint Anthony
statue for us back then.

230
00:18:40,619 --> 00:18:41,537
That’s right, sir!

231
00:18:42,204 --> 00:18:44,039
I stole the statue myself.

232
00:18:44,540 --> 00:18:46,625
[sinister music playing]

233
00:19:00,389 --> 00:19:01,515
[Red] I couldn't care less.

234
00:19:01,598 --> 00:19:03,517
Who are you, and why are you here?

235
00:19:04,810 --> 00:19:09,523
Sir, he has a lead on the idiot
who meddled in our operations.

236
00:19:09,606 --> 00:19:10,858
Anyway, sir,

237
00:19:10,941 --> 00:19:14,403
people in our town have been talking
about who returned the statue,

238
00:19:14,987 --> 00:19:16,572
and they suspect it was someone
who used to be in the army.

239
00:19:16,655 --> 00:19:20,284
I mean, only someone with that kind
of training could have pulled it off.

240
00:19:20,367 --> 00:19:21,952
Quit beating around the bush.

241
00:19:22,661 --> 00:19:24,663
Who's the guy?
Also, what took you so long to tell us?

242
00:19:26,331 --> 00:19:29,835
Sir, he's the son of our tailor.

243
00:19:30,711 --> 00:19:31,837
His name is Atoy.

244
00:19:31,920 --> 00:19:33,672
[dramatic flourish]

245
00:19:36,258 --> 00:19:37,551
Where can I find this Atoy?

246
00:19:37,634 --> 00:19:38,468
‪[music concludes]

247
00:19:41,054 --> 00:19:43,348
- The Goto here is amazing.
- Mmm!

248
00:19:43,432 --> 00:19:45,434
Hey, do you remember?

249
00:19:45,517 --> 00:19:46,852
This was your mom's favorite.

250
00:19:46,935 --> 00:19:49,271
- We always had it after church.
- Yes.

251
00:19:51,064 --> 00:19:52,774
How could I ever forget that?

252
00:19:53,525 --> 00:19:55,527
You'd have your Goto,
and I'd have my Pares.

253
00:19:55,611 --> 00:19:56,778
Exactly! [chuckles]

254
00:19:56,862 --> 00:19:59,907
I remember how I would always
order the same thing.

255
00:19:59,990 --> 00:20:02,618
- Ah, that's right!
- And whenever we got home…

256
00:20:02,701 --> 00:20:04,119
[in unison] Let's race to the bathroom!

257
00:20:04,203 --> 00:20:05,787
[laughing]

258
00:20:05,871 --> 00:20:07,539
- [Fely] Delfin!
- [mutters] Hmm?

259
00:20:07,623 --> 00:20:09,958
How are you doing?

260
00:20:10,959 --> 00:20:11,960
Wait, is this Atoy?

261
00:20:12,878 --> 00:20:14,296
Wow!

262
00:20:14,379 --> 00:20:15,672
It's a good thing
you're finally back, dear.

263
00:20:15,756 --> 00:20:17,424
- Uh… [chuckles]
- He looks exactly like Julie.

264
00:20:17,507 --> 00:20:18,967
Yes. Fely, when did you get here?

265
00:20:19,051 --> 00:20:20,093
Oh, Atoy…

266
00:20:20,177 --> 00:20:21,303
- Dad.
- Do you remember Fely?

267
00:20:21,386 --> 00:20:23,472
- Hmm.
- She's Bunda's mother.

268
00:20:23,555 --> 00:20:25,057
- Hmm.
- [chuckles softly]

269
00:20:25,140 --> 00:20:26,433
I just got here last night.

270
00:20:26,516 --> 00:20:29,311
Anyway, a lot has already
happened here, hasn't it?

271
00:20:29,394 --> 00:20:30,812
- Hmm.
- [Fely] Oh, and by the way,

272
00:20:30,896 --> 00:20:32,439
I brought some chocolate for you guys.

273
00:20:32,522 --> 00:20:34,399
- I'll have someone send it over later.
- [Delfin] Oh, thank you…

274
00:20:34,483 --> 00:20:35,943
Also, I'm not going back
to Hong Kong anymore.

275
00:20:36,026 --> 00:20:36,860
Why is that?

276
00:20:36,944 --> 00:20:38,528
Well, as much as I can,

277
00:20:38,612 --> 00:20:39,947
I want to keep an eye on my little girl.

278
00:20:40,614 --> 00:20:43,325
You know, I've retired from being an OFW.

279
00:20:43,408 --> 00:20:45,619
- Hmm.
- Mom…

280
00:20:45,702 --> 00:20:48,914
I don't remember them asking
about your life story.

281
00:20:48,997 --> 00:20:50,624
- Come on, Mom, let's go.
- [mutters]

282
00:20:50,707 --> 00:20:52,000
We're interrupting their bonding moment.

283
00:20:52,084 --> 00:20:53,043
Just a moment.

284
00:20:53,126 --> 00:20:54,920
I've missed the people here.

285
00:20:55,003 --> 00:20:56,171
[indistinct chattering]

286
00:20:56,255 --> 00:20:57,256
- Let's just go!
- Okay, fine.

287
00:20:57,339 --> 00:20:58,840
- My little girl already wants me to leave.
- [Delfin] All right, go on.

288
00:20:58,924 --> 00:20:59,758
I wasn't done talking to them!

289
00:20:59,841 --> 00:21:01,093
- Mom, can you please…
- But, Mom!

290
00:21:01,176 --> 00:21:02,552
- Chika, I think you need a nap.
- That's so Fely.

291
00:21:02,636 --> 00:21:05,806
- [Bunda] Come on!
- Bunda's mom hasn't changed one bit.

292
00:21:05,889 --> 00:21:07,516
- Hmm, still as noisy as ever.
- Talkative as usual.

293
00:21:07,599 --> 00:21:12,604
[laughing]

294
00:21:12,688 --> 00:21:14,648
- I doubt she'll ever change.
- I agree.

295
00:21:15,232 --> 00:21:16,275
Oh my.

296
00:21:16,900 --> 00:21:18,110
Oh.

297
00:21:18,193 --> 00:21:19,903
[sentimental music playing]

298
00:21:19,987 --> 00:21:22,906
Wait. Your button’s coming loose.

299
00:21:23,490 --> 00:21:25,367
Make sure you fix it
and sew it securely right away.

300
00:21:25,450 --> 00:21:27,536
Don’t worry, it’s still holding up strong.

301
00:21:27,619 --> 00:21:28,704
[chuckles]

302
00:21:33,500 --> 00:21:34,876
- What is it?
- Sir.

303
00:21:35,585 --> 00:21:37,129
Atoy is here.

304
00:21:37,212 --> 00:21:40,173
I told you so. He comes here
every Sunday without fail.

305
00:21:42,843 --> 00:21:44,011
Here, look, look.

306
00:21:47,431 --> 00:21:50,309
Dad, this pomelo looks
pretty good too. Do you want it?

307
00:21:51,351 --> 00:21:54,104
- Sure, it looks sweet.
- Keep the change.

308
00:21:54,187 --> 00:21:55,480
Wait, let's grab one.

309
00:21:55,564 --> 00:21:57,441
Okay. Thanks.

310
00:21:59,026 --> 00:22:00,986
There he is. Yes, that's him.

311
00:22:01,695 --> 00:22:02,696
The guy who just crossed the street?

312
00:22:03,280 --> 00:22:05,032
I think we should take one.

313
00:22:05,115 --> 00:22:06,366
I wonder how much it weighs.

314
00:22:12,706 --> 00:22:14,082
[brooding music playing]

315
00:22:39,524 --> 00:22:40,942
[tires screeching in distance]

316
00:22:44,696 --> 00:22:45,864
[car revving in distance]

317
00:22:45,947 --> 00:22:47,657
[brake squeals]

318
00:22:47,741 --> 00:22:49,910
- [thuds]
- [tires screeching]

319
00:22:51,495 --> 00:22:53,538
[overlapping chatter]

320
00:22:57,751 --> 00:22:58,960
Dad?

321
00:23:02,130 --> 00:23:03,673
Please, call an ambulance! Please, please!

322
00:23:03,757 --> 00:23:05,300
We need an ambulance! Dad?

323
00:23:05,383 --> 00:23:07,886
[overlapping chatter]

324
00:23:07,969 --> 00:23:09,179
[Atoy] Dad… Dad…

325
00:23:09,262 --> 00:23:11,389
[Atoy whispering]

326
00:23:11,473 --> 00:23:12,891
[tires screeching in distance]

327
00:23:14,392 --> 00:23:15,727
What a dimwit!

328
00:23:16,394 --> 00:23:17,229
Sir.

329
00:23:18,480 --> 00:23:20,649
Sir, you just ran over Atoy's father.

330
00:23:21,900 --> 00:23:23,235
I think you might have killed him.

331
00:23:24,986 --> 00:23:26,655
Sir, the man is innocent.

332
00:23:27,989 --> 00:23:29,908
[car revving]

333
00:23:31,451 --> 00:23:32,619
[Mongki] Sir, where are we headed?

334
00:23:33,662 --> 00:23:34,955
We're going to see Lucas.

335
00:23:35,038 --> 00:23:36,706
We'll have him distroy this car.

336
00:23:36,790 --> 00:23:39,167
No! What a waste!
This car's too good to scrap.

337
00:23:40,252 --> 00:23:41,795
Do you want us to get in trouble?

338
00:23:45,715 --> 00:23:49,136
Psst, go talk to your friend.
I think the cat's got his tongue.

339
00:23:49,886 --> 00:23:52,430
Hey. Psst! Just take it easy.

340
00:23:53,014 --> 00:23:54,724
You're not going to get in trouble,
if that's what you're worried about.

341
00:23:55,934 --> 00:23:58,270
Sir, I think you might
have killed Atoy's father.

342
00:23:59,104 --> 00:24:00,647
He's innocent.

343
00:24:00,730 --> 00:24:02,190
He was a good man.

344
00:24:03,817 --> 00:24:05,443
Find out if he's really dead.

345
00:24:06,486 --> 00:24:07,821
If he is, serves him right.

346
00:24:08,864 --> 00:24:10,490
His life was the price
for his son's mistakes.

347
00:24:14,744 --> 00:24:19,791
[intense music playing]

348
00:24:22,127 --> 00:24:24,087
- [overlapping chatter]
- [man] Help!

349
00:24:24,171 --> 00:24:27,299
Help, help us, call an ambulance, please!
Please, please!

350
00:24:28,758 --> 00:24:30,802
Call an ambulance, please, please!
Faster, please!

351
00:24:30,886 --> 00:24:31,928
[woman] Someone has already
called an ambulance.

352
00:24:32,012 --> 00:24:33,305
[man] Sir, we've already
called an ambulance.

353
00:24:33,388 --> 00:24:34,848
Let's just wait for them.
They're already on their way.

354
00:24:34,931 --> 00:24:36,808
Don't forget your button.

355
00:24:37,434 --> 00:24:38,810
[groaning]

356
00:24:38,894 --> 00:24:42,314
Go over the stitches…

357
00:24:42,397 --> 00:24:43,940
‪[woman] Call an ambulance now.

358
00:24:44,024 --> 00:24:46,234
…five or six times.

359
00:24:46,318 --> 00:24:47,277
Yes, I hear you.

360
00:24:47,360 --> 00:24:51,448
For it to last,

361
00:24:51,531 --> 00:24:55,493
so it won't come loose or fall off.

362
00:24:55,577 --> 00:24:56,828
Okay. [stammering]

363
00:24:56,912 --> 00:24:57,954
Just leave it to me.

364
00:24:58,038 --> 00:25:00,415
- Is the ambulance here yet?!
- [woman] Not yet.

365
00:25:00,498 --> 00:25:02,125
[man] It's on its way!

366
00:25:02,209 --> 00:25:04,252
An ambulance is on its way!

367
00:25:04,336 --> 00:25:06,713
Dad, hang in there!

368
00:25:07,464 --> 00:25:09,507
Please, don't move, and stay with me.

369
00:25:09,591 --> 00:25:13,762
This might be…

370
00:25:16,681 --> 00:25:22,479
the last time I can help you…

371
00:25:23,230 --> 00:25:27,651
I’m just trying to make the most
of our final moments together…

372
00:25:27,734 --> 00:25:31,279
Dad, Dad, Dad, don't say that.

373
00:25:31,363 --> 00:25:33,281
[overlapping chatter]

374
00:25:33,365 --> 00:25:34,199
Dad?

375
00:25:36,201 --> 00:25:37,160
Dad!

376
00:25:37,869 --> 00:25:40,705
Okay, okay.

377
00:25:40,789 --> 00:25:45,418
[melancholic music playing]

378
00:25:46,753 --> 00:25:48,672
- Dad?
- [groaning]

379
00:25:50,215 --> 00:25:51,091
Dad?

380
00:25:51,174 --> 00:25:54,803
- [melancholic music continues]
- [overlapping chatter]

381
00:26:00,684 --> 00:26:02,310
[sobbing]

382
00:26:09,317 --> 00:26:11,361
Dad? [sobbing]

383
00:26:35,510 --> 00:26:39,681
[electronic blipping]

384
00:26:45,979 --> 00:26:47,897
- [Karla] Excuse me!
- [screams]

385
00:26:47,981 --> 00:26:48,898
- Hey!
- [clamoring]

386
00:26:48,982 --> 00:26:50,191
[man shouts] Oh, no!

387
00:26:50,275 --> 00:26:51,234
[woman] What gives, Karla?!

388
00:26:51,318 --> 00:26:52,193
I'm really sorry.

389
00:26:52,944 --> 00:26:54,446
Hey, give me my phone back!

390
00:26:54,529 --> 00:26:56,823
[Atoy] <i>Wow, she really is small</i>
<i>but terrible.</i>

391
00:26:56,906 --> 00:26:58,033
<i>Downright terrible.</i>

392
00:26:58,116 --> 00:27:00,201
Come on, you're so tiny, yet…

393
00:27:00,285 --> 00:27:01,328
Tell me, do you have a problem
with small people?

394
00:27:01,411 --> 00:27:02,829
[Ranger] <i>For your next mission,</i>

395
00:27:02,912 --> 00:27:06,124
our VIP client wants us
to track this down.

396
00:27:06,207 --> 00:27:07,542
[goon] <i>Maybe you’ll want</i>
<i>to place a bet.</i>

397
00:27:07,625 --> 00:27:09,169
The new fighters have arrived.

398
00:27:09,252 --> 00:27:11,921
[announcer] Challenging our champion,

399
00:27:12,005 --> 00:27:14,799
none other than…

400
00:27:14,883 --> 00:27:19,054
Amazing Ame!

401
00:27:19,137 --> 00:27:20,221
UP NEXT

402
00:27:20,305 --> 00:27:21,222
[honks]

403
00:27:22,640 --> 00:27:25,560
[intense music playing]

404
00:27:31,775 --> 00:27:34,194
Subtitle translation by:
Inocencio Cañete Raman Jr.
